<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1195,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,544,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">Report as epibiont on bryozoans:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wailes, G. H." box="[549,705,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553" refId="ref8024" refString="Wailes, G. H. (1943) Canadian Pacific fauna. 1. Protozoa. 1 f. Ciliata. 1 g. Suctoria. University of Toronto Press, Toronro, 46 pp." type="book" year="1943">Wailes (1943)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wright" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[811,1009,1195,1221]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Vaginicolidae" genus="Thuricola" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Peritrichida" pageId="6" pageNumber="553" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="valvata">
<emphasis box="[811,1009,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">Thuricola valvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as epibiont on bryozoans from Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[246,333,1231,1257]" name="Canada" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">Canada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[344,537,1231,1257]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mccauley, J. E. &amp; Hancock, D. R." box="[552,867,1231,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553" pagination="8" refId="ref7154" refString="Mccauley, J. E. &amp; Hancock, D. R. (1971) Appendix 8. Annotated checklist of plants and animals. In: Oceanography of the Nearshore Coastal Waters of the Pacific Northwest. Vol. 2. Oregon State University, Corvallis, Oregon, pp. 165 - 744." type="book chapter" year="1971">Mccauley &amp; Hancock 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1195,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,615,1267,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">Report as epibiont on other hosts:</emphasis>
The species is characteristic as cosmopolite (
<bibRefCitation author="Kahl, A." box="[1139,1263,1267,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553" pagination="651 - 886" refId="ref6874" refString="Kahl, A. (1935) Wimpertiere oder Ciliata (lnfusoria), eine Bearbeitung der freilebenden und ectocommensalen Infusorien der Erde, unter Ausschlussder marinen Tintinnidae. 4. Peritricha und Chonotricha. In: Grimpe, G. &amp; Wagler, E. (Eds.), Die Tierwelt der Nord und Ostsee, 30, pp. 651 - 886." type="journal article" year="1935">Kahl 1935</bibRefCitation>
), inhabiting on algae, Bryozoa and other marine organisms. It was also reported from freshwaters of 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1196,1303,1329]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="553">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gassovsky, G. M." box="[1211,1401,1303,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="553" pagination="58 - 90" refId="ref6456" refString="Gassovsky, G. M. (1960) Praktychne znachennya infuzorij ta istoriya ikh doslidzhennya na Ukraini. Zbirnik pratc' Zoologichnogo muzeyu, 29, 58 - 90. [in Ukrainian]" type="journal article" year="1960">Gassovsky 1960</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
